This script is supposed to run on a newly installed ubuntu-mini,
in order to configure the distro to my liking.
This script should do steps:

1) install software from APT
2) configure openbox
    2.1) autostart
    2.2) rc.xml
    2.3) right-click menu 
3) configure xfce4-panel
4) theming
    4.1) dark theme
    4.2) icon pack
    4.3) wallpaper
5) configure libreoffice
6) configure vim